<l>nīṭa varutal ceyyuḷu ḷurittē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is appropriate that the lengthened forms occur in poetry.<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">ceyyuḷuḷ ;</foreign> e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">āyiru tiṇai = anta iru tiṇai (Tol. Col. 1).</foreign></note></l>
<l>Even if a vowel follows, that rule is not affected.<note place="foot">Exx. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">a + āṭai &gt; avvāṭai ; a + ilai &gt; avvilai.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
